properties.name: Norwood Junction
properties.wheelchair:description: To access any platforms except platform 1 there is only stair access. There are about 15 stairs to access the platforms.

properties.name: Leatherhead
properties.wheelchair:description: Ramp to Booking Office entrance west side, for London, manual doors. Accessible toilet (key). Long roadside ramps to east side platform. Hearing Loop.

properties.name: Teddington
properties.source:name: local knowledge
properties.wheelchair:description: Level access to both platforms from street but bridge between platforms not wheelchair accessible.

properties.name: Custom House
properties.wheelchair:description: Alle von uns benutzten DLR-Stationen (Docklands Light Railway) waren mit Aufzügen ausgestattet. Der Zugang vom Bahnsteig in die Züge ist mit dem Rollstuhl problemlos möglich.

properties.name: Wembley Stadium
properties.note: This station has wheelchair access, but wheelchair users may require assistance as it is via a gravel path.

properties.name: Reigate
properties.wheelchair:description: Step to Booking Office and Accessible toilet. Hearing Loop in Booking Office. Platform 2 for Reading & London step free. Platform 1 for Gatwick: step free via locked gate when ticket office open. FREE Blue Badge Bays in car park 100m from Platform 2.

properties.name: West Ruislip
properties.source: NPE, and wikipedia description for which goes on which side

properties.name: Dalston Junction
properties.wheelchair:description: Wide gates, lift down to all plaforms, Radar key operated wheelchair accessible toilet near lift at ticket hall level.

properties.name: Sidcup
properties.wheelchair:description: Entrance depends on which platform you need to access, only the London bound platform is accessible from the station building itself, the other platform is accessed via a separate entrance on the far side

properties.description: This station has Wadsworth lifts modernised by Otis.

King's Cross St. Pancras
properties.name:he: תחנת הרכבת התחתית קינגס קרוס סיינט פנקראס
properties.note: Official name: King's Cross St. Pancras Underground Station
properties.wikipedia: en:King's Cross St. Pancras tube station

properties.name: Abbey Road
properties.note: NOT the Abbey Road from Beatles (see St John's Wood station).

properties.name: Addlestone
properties.wheelchair:description: Both platforms accessible by ramps from street. Only automatic ticket sales. Access to opposite platform via level crossing.

properties.name: Greenford
properties.note: Surrounding lines made sense of with help from http://www.roscalen.com/signals/Greenford/index.htm

properties.name: Edgware Road (Circle Line)
properties.wikipedia: en:Edgware Road tube station (Circle, District and Hammersmith & City lines)

properties.name: Hampton
properties.note: Platform 1 is Clapham Junction and London Waterloo bound; Platform 2 is Shepperton bound

properties.name: Chalfont & Latimer
properties.note: Chiltern Line and Metropolitan Line Station

properties.name: Merstham
properties.wheelchair:description:
No access from Platform 1, Booking office and car park to Platform 2 (towards Gatwick and coast). 
Train ramp NOT available all day.
Loop not working (3/16)

properties.name: Sutton
properties.wheelchair:description: Lifts to all platforms. Accessible toilets on Platforms 1 & 2/3. Also ChangingPlaces Toilet on 2/3. http://changingplaces.uktoiletmap.org/toilet/view/620 - Station supervisor is able to offer a key to non-travellers.

properties.name: Horsley
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free from parking to trains from London, & to Guildford. Steep approach from village and bus stops not step-free. 1 dedicated Blue Badge space near entrance.

properties.name: Betchworth
properties.wheelchair:description: Unstaffed station, ramps available for use by train crew. Steep ramps up onto platforms both sides. Gate to Gatwick trains easy to open. Nearby road has no footway.

properties.name: Woking
properties.wheelchair:description: Lifts at west end footbridge. Accessible toilets on platforms 3/4 & 5 (1/2 not checked for toilet). Some dedicated Blue Badge spaces near south entrance.

properties.name: Dorking Deepdene
properties.wheelchair:description: Unstaffed. Long flights of steps from both platforms to Road for interchange with Dorking North station.

properties.name: Redhill
properties.wheelchair:description: Blue Badge spaces (2). Ramps to ticket office and tactile map of station. Lifts to all platforms. Accessible toilet (RADAR KEY) on Platform 3. Defibrillator in subway by lift to platforms 1+2.

properties.name: Bexley
properties.wheelchair:description: Only the near platform (to Crayford) is accessible

properties.name: London Bridge (Rail)
properties.wheelchair:description: Step-free from Bus station. New wheelchair refuge areas and Hearing Loop enabled announcements on terminal platform 10 shown, and above. (2017)

properties.name: West Ruislip
properties.source: NPE, and wikipedia description for which goes on which side

properties.name: Rickmansworth
properties.note: Chiltern Line and Metropolitan Line Station
